The paper discusses a novel solution for network slicing brokering, which involves the allocation and redistribution of network resources among tenants in a secure and automated manner. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and network security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper leverages blockchain technology, which is a distributed system (cs.DC) and involves consensus algorithms (cs.Distributed). Finally, the paper also addresses the needs of industry verticals, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
